  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/4141",
  "title": "queryHook is broken ",
  "body": "**Describe the bug 🐛**\r\n\r\nThe option `queryHook` on `SearchBox` is broken since the version [3.2.0](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/develop/CHANGELOG.md#320-2019-03-14). The widget is not updated correctly, stalled data override the latest keystrokes. I've tested with version 3.1.1 and we don't have the issue, it made me think that the `SearchBox` rewrite is the problem.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce 🔍**\r\n\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n\r\n1. Go to https://codesandbox.io/s/instantsearchjs-queryhook-issue-n04f7\r\n2. Enable the network throttling\r\n3. Type into the `SearchBox`\r\n4. After some delay the latest character are overridden\r\n\r\nWithout the network throttling, the issue is present too. But it's easier to reproduce with it. \r\n\r\n**Screenshots 🖥**\r\n\r\n![Untitled](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6513513/65584414-22da0700-df81-11e9-812e-6fee6a4e6642.gif)\r\n",
